You should parse the value to number in order to get the value as a number as you don&#39;t have `price` attribute that store the value.

    setPrice(Number(e.target.value));

Also, you can change the type of the input to number as well

**HTML has exactly one data type: Text (string).**

All values extracted from HTML elements are strings. If you need a value to be treated differently, it will be up to your JavaScript to convert the type. For numeric data, there are several ways, but perhaps the simplest is to prepend an arithmetic operator, [like `+`][1] to the value.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    let input = document.querySelector(&quot;input&quot;);

    input.addEventListener(&quot;blur&quot;, function(){
      console.log(&quot;Data is: &quot; + typeof input.value);
      console.log(&quot;Converted type is: &quot; + typeof +input.value);
    });

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    Enter a number and press TAB: &lt;input type=&quot;number&quot;&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

If your data begins with a number but also has non-numeric characters following it, then [`parseInt()`][2] and [`parseFloat()`][3] will extract the number and stop when non-numeric values are found:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    let input = document.querySelector(&quot;input&quot;);

    input.addEventListener(&quot;blur&quot;, function(){
      console.log(&quot;Data is: &quot; + typeof input.value);
      // It&#39;s a best-practice to always specify the second argument for parseInt()
      // to ensure the correct conversion.
      console.log(&quot;Converted type is: &quot; + typeof parseInt(input.value, 10));
    });

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    Enter a number and press TAB: &lt;input type=&quot;number&quot;&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://scotch.io/tutorials/javascript-unary-operators-simple-and-useful#toc-unary-plus-
  [2]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/parseInt
  [3]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/parseFloat

